title: Count Your Blessings 12
body:
Pairing: Steve Rogers x Reader

Warnings: Language. Lies. Friends with Benefits. Possessiveness. Fights. Kidnapping. Small amount of violence.

OKAY!! Just a heads up there is no abuse in this story from Steve. He’s written as an alpha male. Yes he’s possessive of his family and the woman he loves, but NOT ABUSIVE. If you’re reading that, than we really need to have a long talk so feel free to send me a message.

TAG LIST: If your name is crossed out. Check your settings before I remove you from the list. Please and Thank you. I did remove peaches, because I can’t tag them just an FYI.

“Damn I’ve missed you.” He chuckles, leaning in to kiss you.

“Brad.” You put up a hand, confused and nervous. Fuck Steve would be here any moment, he had to go or this was going to fucking ugly.

“What, you don’t look happy to see me.” He sighs. “I know things have been distant, this job has me beyond busy and I didn’t want to distract you during finals. I thought we could de-stress together.” He grins, moving towards you again.

“Can’t. Sorry you have to go.” You push him back.

“I figured Ari was with your mom, tonight. Some of the girls mentioned you were going out.” He looks confused.

“We are. But um, that’s not why you have to go.” You scramble. Fuck he had to leave. “You know the rules, you can’t just show up at my place without letting me know first. I need you to leave. Now.” You stare him down.

“I didn’t think it would be a big deal, Ari isn’t home.” He shrugs.

“Right well Ari isn’t but look this isn’t a serious thing between us. You need to know Ari’s dad is back, were giving things a try again.” You explain.

“Are you fucking kidding me?” Brad scuffs at you.

“He’s her father, and honestly I never got over him, not like I thought.” You explain, your hand holding your robe closed at the top.

“He’s going to fuck you over again.” He warns you.

“And I’m a grown up, I can handle that.” You bite back.

“Fine. Call me when you realize you fucked up.” He stomps down the steps. You hear the sound of Steve’s bike when Brad reaches his truck.

“Fuck.” You wince. Brads in his truck and backing out. Steve pauses in the street to let him go, but he’s staring at you the whole time. “Oh fuck.” You groan. Once Brad passes and turns the corner, Steve pulls into the drive and rolls around your SUV in the drive, before parking in front of it. The bike shuts off and it’s quiet accept for the guilt ripping at you as you wait. He’s up the porch steps in a few strides, backing you into the house.

“Who was that?” He points back as he kicks the door closed behind him. He hadn’t unzipped his black hoodie, pulled off his gloves, or fixed his hair.

“Ummm. That friend I was telling you about.” You admit.

“Okay.” He takes a deep breath, pinching the bridge of his nose. “Explain it, before I jump to conclusions.” He grumbles.

“So I was showering, when I got out, I heard knocking.” You start quickly.

“Explaining the robe.” He nods, staring down at you.

“Right. I thought it was you, thinking maybe you had left your key in the truck or something.” You nod, he nods back. “So, when I opened it without peeking, it was him and he was standing there and he I don’t know assumed something.” You wave your hand around letting go of the opening of your robe. “He was trying to hook up, but I told him you were back. Well not you, but Ari’s dad was back, and we were trying again.” You nod, letting out the breath you’d been holding.

“And he left?” He stares at you.

“Sort of.” Your nose scrunches up. “He had some nasty things to say, disgruntled you know. But he’s never shown up here without calling or texting me to make sure he could. But apparently, he knew Ari wasn’t home, something about the girls at the diner mentioned we were all going out. So, he thought it was okay.” You run a hand through your wet hair.

“I know what he drives now.” Steve stares unblinking blue eyes at you.

“Okay.” You nod, understanding.

“Get ready.” He points at the stairs, you turn heading up the stairs quickly.  Grateful to be avoiding a full blown argument with Steve.



“Lifted. Red. I don’t give a fuck what his name is. It’s a pretty boys truck.” Steve’s grumbling into the phone.

When she steps out of the bathroom, he pauses looking over at her. She wore ripped, black skinny jeans, tucked into black ankle boots, her shirt is sleeveless, grey, reading Whiskey Bent and Hell Bound. The end of it tied up resting at the waist of her jeans, the sides cut down and wide, the sides of her black bra are visible. Her hair falls in loose curls as she shakes it out over one shoulder, making him stare. “Call me if you see it.” He mutters, hanging up.

“What was that about?” She looks over at him.

“Nothing. Damn babe, you know how to distract a guy.” He grins at her.

“Good maybe you’ll stop worrying about other guys and remember who’s bringing my ass home tonight.” She grins at him, he stands up ready to follow her out of the room.

“Damn right.” He slips his hands over his hips as he follows her out of their room.



Wanda whistles as Steve helps you from your SUV. You laugh, lacing your fingers with his own tugging him along.

“My, my, did you bring enough candy for the rest of the group?” She grins eyeing Steve.

“No, but he did invite friends.” You wink at her.

“You’re my new favorite.” She grins at him, he laughs following the two of you into the bar. He was allowed to wear his kutte inside, as long as there was no turf issues, according to the bouncer outside.

“No man, we coexist and have no problems.” Steve smirks.

“That’s what I like to hear.” The bouncer chuckles, waving you through.

Jaime, Gwen and a few other girls are already inside. You quickly introduce Steve, they introduce the two boyfriends with them. Wanda asks what the two of you are drinking.

“Water.” Steve chuckles.

“Same.” You grin.

“She’ll have Gin and lemon lime soda.” Steve yells over the music at Wanda.

“Oh I just love you.” Wanda taps her pointer finger on Steve’s nose. “I’ll be back!” She yells moving through the people.

“Gin?” You tip your head.

“I remember what my girls likes.” He laughs.

“You better be taking care of Ari tomorrow.” You laugh.

“Got it covered.” He winks, kissing you.

“Suck face later, drink with me now!” Wanda pulls them apart handing over a bottle of water to Steve and a tall glass with ice and clear liquid to you.

trail.content:
Pairing: Steve Rogers x Reader

Warnings: Language. Lies. Friends with Benefits. Possessiveness. Fights. Kidnapping. Small amount of violence.

OKAY!! Just a heads up there is no abuse in this story from Steve. He’s written as an alpha male. Yes he’s possessive of his family and the woman he loves, but NOT ABUSIVE. If you’re reading that, than we really need to have a long talk so feel free to send me a message.

TAG LIST: If your name is crossed out. Check your settings before I remove you from the list. Please and Thank you. I did remove peaches, because I can’t tag them just an FYI.

“Damn I’ve missed you.” He chuckles, leaning in to kiss you.

“Brad.” You put up a hand, confused and nervous. Fuck Steve would be here any moment, he had to go or this was going to fucking ugly.

“What, you don’t look happy to see me.” He sighs. “I know things have been distant, this job has me beyond busy and I didn’t want to distract you during finals. I thought we could de-stress together.” He grins, moving towards you again.

“Can’t. Sorry you have to go.” You push him back.

“I figured Ari was with your mom, tonight. Some of the girls mentioned you were going out.” He looks confused.

“We are. But um, that’s not why you have to go.” You scramble. Fuck he had to leave. “You know the rules, you can’t just show up at my place without letting me know first. I need you to leave. Now.” You stare him down.

“I didn’t think it would be a big deal, Ari isn’t home.” He shrugs.

“Right well Ari isn’t but look this isn’t a serious thing between us. You need to know Ari’s dad is back, were giving things a try again.” You explain.

“Are you fucking kidding me?” Brad scuffs at you.

“He’s her father, and honestly I never got over him, not like I thought.” You explain, your hand holding your robe closed at the top.

“He’s going to fuck you over again.” He warns you.

“And I’m a grown up, I can handle that.” You bite back.

“Fine. Call me when you realize you fucked up.” He stomps down the steps. You hear the sound of Steve’s bike when Brad reaches his truck.

“Fuck.” You wince. Brads in his truck and backing out. Steve pauses in the street to let him go, but he’s staring at you the whole time. “Oh fuck.” You groan. Once Brad passes and turns the corner, Steve pulls into the drive and rolls around your SUV in the drive, before parking in front of it. The bike shuts off and it’s quiet accept for the guilt ripping at you as you wait. He’s up the porch steps in a few strides, backing you into the house.

“Who was that?” He points back as he kicks the door closed behind him. He hadn’t unzipped his black hoodie, pulled off his gloves, or fixed his hair.

“Ummm. That friend I was telling you about.” You admit.

“Okay.” He takes a deep breath, pinching the bridge of his nose. “Explain it, before I jump to conclusions.” He grumbles.

“So I was showering, when I got out, I heard knocking.” You start quickly.

“Explaining the robe.” He nods, staring down at you.

“Right. I thought it was you, thinking maybe you had left your key in the truck or something.” You nod, he nods back. “So, when I opened it without peeking, it was him and he was standing there and he I don’t know assumed something.” You wave your hand around letting go of the opening of your robe. “He was trying to hook up, but I told him you were back. Well not you, but Ari’s dad was back, and we were trying again.” You nod, letting out the breath you’d been holding.

“And he left?” He stares at you.

“Sort of.” Your nose scrunches up. “He had some nasty things to say, disgruntled you know. But he’s never shown up here without calling or texting me to make sure he could. But apparently, he knew Ari wasn’t home, something about the girls at the diner mentioned we were all going out. So, he thought it was okay.” You run a hand through your wet hair.

“I know what he drives now.” Steve stares unblinking blue eyes at you.

“Okay.” You nod, understanding.

“Get ready.” He points at the stairs, you turn heading up the stairs quickly.  Grateful to be avoiding a full blown argument with Steve.



“Lifted. Red. I don’t give a fuck what his name is. It’s a pretty boys truck.” Steve’s grumbling into the phone.

When she steps out of the bathroom, he pauses looking over at her. She wore ripped, black skinny jeans, tucked into black ankle boots, her shirt is sleeveless, grey, reading Whiskey Bent and Hell Bound. The end of it tied up resting at the waist of her jeans, the sides cut down and wide, the sides of her black bra are visible. Her hair falls in loose curls as she shakes it out over one shoulder, making him stare. “Call me if you see it.” He mutters, hanging up.

“What was that about?” She looks over at him.

“Nothing. Damn babe, you know how to distract a guy.” He grins at her.

“Good maybe you’ll stop worrying about other guys and remember who’s bringing my ass home tonight.” She grins at him, he stands up ready to follow her out of the room.

“Damn right.” He slips his hands over his hips as he follows her out of their room.



Wanda whistles as Steve helps you from your SUV. You laugh, lacing your fingers with his own tugging him along.

“My, my, did you bring enough candy for the rest of the group?” She grins eyeing Steve.

“No, but he did invite friends.” You wink at her.

“You’re my new favorite.” She grins at him, he laughs following the two of you into the bar. He was allowed to wear his kutte inside, as long as there was no turf issues, according to the bouncer outside.

“No man, we coexist and have no problems.” Steve smirks.

“That’s what I like to hear.” The bouncer chuckles, waving you through.

Jaime, Gwen and a few other girls are already inside. You quickly introduce Steve, they introduce the two boyfriends with them. Wanda asks what the two of you are drinking.

“Water.” Steve chuckles.

“Same.” You grin.

“She’ll have Gin and lemon lime soda.” Steve yells over the music at Wanda.

“Oh I just love you.” Wanda taps her pointer finger on Steve’s nose. “I’ll be back!” She yells moving through the people.

“Gin?” You tip your head.

“I remember what my girls likes.” He laughs.

“You better be taking care of Ari tomorrow.” You laugh.

“Got it covered.” He winks, kissing you.

“Suck face later, drink with me now!” Wanda pulls them apart handing over a bottle of water to Steve and a tall glass with ice and clear liquid to you.

summary: Hey, who’s the character in your profile pic?
question: Hey, who’s the character in your profile pic?
answer:
It’s Victor Mancha, from the new Runaways series. 

He’s a robot built by Ultron with the purpose of killing the Avengers, but he was raised human and turned good. Recently, he was “killed” in the Vision comic series, but in Runaways they’re trying to fix him. So far, they’ve only fixed his head.

He’s super cool and funny. Very chill guy. 

I totally recommend reading the Runaways. It’s one of my favorites of the year, and the art is amazing. 

You can read it here.
